# Page Template: Form Page

This template describes the structure, data flow, and component breakdown for a **form page** (create or edit) in {{ display_name }}. Use it for any page that accepts user input and POSTs or PATCHes to the Symfony API.

---

## Purpose

A form page collects user input, validates it on the client side for UX, and submits it to the Symfony API. The API performs authoritative validation and returns either the created/updated entity or a 422 with field-level errors. The form maps these errors back to the correct fields without a full page reload.

**Critical principle:** Client-side validation is a UX optimization, not a security measure. The Symfony Validator is the source of truth. Never skip server-side validation because the frontend "already checked".

---

## Two Modes: Create vs. Edit

The same component handles both modes. The difference:

| Mode | URL | HTTP method | Initial data |
|------|-----|------------|-------------|
| Create | `/users/new` | `POST /api/users` | Empty form |
| Edit | `/users/[id]/edit` | `PATCH /api/users/[id]` | Pre-populated from `GET /api/users/[id]` |

In edit mode, the Server Component fetches the existing entity and passes it as `defaultValues` to the form component.

---

## Data Flow

### Create

```
User fills form
  └── Client Component handles state
        └── Submit button clicked
              └── POST /api/users  { name, email, role }
                    ├── 201 Created   ─► router.push('/users/new-id')
                    └── 422 Unprocessable ─► map violations to field errors
```

### Edit

```
Page loads
  └── Server Component: GET /api/users/[id]
        └── Pass entity as defaultValues to form

User edits, submits
  └── PATCH /api/users/[id]  { email: "new@email.com" }
        ├── 200 OK   ─► router.refresh() and show success toast
        └── 422     ─► map violations to field errors
```

---

## URL

```
/users/new               # create
/users/[id]/edit         # edit
```

